## 2026-04-03 - Unify PreviewPanel and TokenDetailPreview into context-aware preview pane
- Made the split-view PreviewPanel context-aware: when a token is focused (`previewingToken` is set), it renders `TokenDetailPreview` inline in the bottom pane instead of collection templates. When nothing is focused, it renders the normal collection templates (Colors, Type Scale, Buttons, etc.).
- **PreviewPanel.tsx**: Added `focusedToken`, `pathToSet`, `onClearFocus`, and `onEditToken` props to the interface. Imported `TokenDetailPreview`. Added an early-return branch that renders `TokenDetailPreview` inline when `focusedToken` is set, with `onClose=onClearFocus` (back to collection) and `onNavigateToAlias` wired to `onNavigateToToken` for alias-chain navigation.
- **App.tsx** (split-view section): Changed `onNavigateToToken` to call `setPreviewingToken` (focus token in preview pane) instead of navigating the list. Added `focusedToken={previewingToken}`, `pathToSet`, `onClearFocus`, and `onEditToken` (which collapses split view and opens editor sidebar) to the PreviewPanel call. Updated split-view TokenList `highlightedToken` to also reflect `previewingToken?.path`.

