## 2026-04-03 - Server route input validation gaps across generators, lint, and search
- Added `isFiniteNum()` helper to `generators.ts` and replaced all `typeof x === 'number'` checks in `validateGeneratorConfig` with `isFiniteNum(x)` вҖ” covers colorRamp steps/lightEnd/darkEnd/chromaBoost/lightnessCurve/sourceStep, typeScale ratio/roundTo/exponents, spacingScale/opacityScale/borderRadiusScale/zIndexScale/shadowScale/customScale numeric step fields, and darkModeInversion chromaBoost.
- Added full schema validation to `PUT /api/lint/config` in `lint.ts`: validates body is a plain object, rejects unknown top-level keys, validates `lintRules` is an object, rejects unknown rule keys, validates `enabled` is boolean, `severity` is one of `error|warning|info`, and `options` is an object.
- Added input length/count limits to `GET /api/tokens/search` in `tokens.ts`: `q` capped at 500 chars, comma-separated list params capped at 20 items each, each item capped at 200 chars.

